						<summary>

						<p>On a slab fixed in the <hi rend="italic">Yajñaśālai-maṇḍapa</hi> on the north side of the second <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> in the temple of Ranganāthasvāmi.</p>						

						<p>1652 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It is dated in Śaka 1572, (expressed in Kaṭapaya system vasumtyēḥ) Nandana Vaiśākha, śu. bhadrā (8), corresponding to April 5, Monday, 1652 A.D.</p>						

						<p>Refers to the construction of a big and elevated Yajñaśālai in the temple of Śrī Raṅg(rāja) by Rāmānuja mahāmuni.</p>						

						</summary>
